# Live tuning overlay layout

The focus-driven tree panel ([cleave/viz_tuning_overlay.py](cleave/viz_tuning_overlay.py), [cleave/viz_tuning_controls.py](cleave/viz_tuning_controls.py)) splits into two vertical sections. Use these names in docs, issues, and UI work.

## Track rows section

The upper block: all rows where `index < track_rows` (`track_rows = len(layer_z_order) * ROWS_PER_TRACK`).

- One **track block** per stem in `layer_z_order`; six rows each (`ROWS_PER_TRACK`).
- Row kinds: `RowKind.TRACK_HEADER`, `TRACK_PRESET_DIR`, `TRACK_PRESET`, `TRACK_BLEND`, `TRACK_OPACITY`, `TRACK_BEAT`.
- Per-stem state: `TrackBlock` in `TuningViewState.tracks`.
- On-screen header label: `Layer N: STEM` (user-facing "layer"; code often says "track").

Say **track rows section** for the whole upper block; **track row** for a single line.

## Footer rows section

The lower block after a visual gap (`footer_gap` in `draw()`): `footer_row_count(state)` rows (3 or 4).

- Row kinds: `RowKind.CONFIG_HEADER` (non-navigable active config path), `RowKind.TRANSPORT`, `SAVE_AS_NEW_CONFIG`, `OVERWRITE_CONFIG` (overwrite only when `allow_overwrite`).
- Constants: `FOOTER_ROWS_WITH_OVERWRITE`, `FOOTER_ROWS_WITHOUT_OVERWRITE`; index via `footer_index = index - track_rows`.

## Whole panel

`TuningOverlay` draws one panel (`panel_rect`). There are no separate section rectangles; layout is positional from the track-rows / footer-rows split.
